      "description": "This 997.1 Carrera is a purist\u2019s specification, featuring the 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six mated to a 6-speed manual transaxle. The M96/05 power plant delivers linear torque across the rev range, benefiting from a recent top-end inspection and a preventative water pump replacement. The chassis retains its factory-spec rigidity, with the MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension providing communicative feedback through the hydraulic steering rack. The braking system features four-piston monobloc calipers with plenty of life left on the cross-drilled rotors. While the exterior shows some light stone chipping on the frontal fascia, the mechanical components are synchronized perfectly for spirited driving. A well-sorted example with a documented service history regarding the IMS and RMS status.",
